SIMPLE: shorling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shorling
<hw>Shor"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The skin
of a sheen after the fleece is shorn off, as distinct from the
<xex>morling</xex>, or skin taken from the dead sheep; also, a sheep of
the first year's shearing.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who is shorn; a shaveling; hence, in
contempt, a priest.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shorn</ent>⟦br⟧
